# Next.js/TypeScript Project Guidelines

## Overview
This is a Next.js project template.

## Tech Stack
- Framework: Next.js 15+
- Language: TypeScript, React 19
- State Management: React Context / Redux Toolkit
- API Layer: Next.js API Routes
- Styling: Tailwind CSS V4
- Testing: Jest and React Testing Library
- Package Manager: pnpm

## Rules
Follow these rules when building the project.

### General Rules
- Use absolute imports for anything within the project unless otherwise specified
- Use PascalCase for components and camelCase for functions/variables
- Dont update third-party libraries unless otherwise specified
- Write components and functions with JSDoc documentation
- Aim for roughly 30 lines of code per component/function
- Keep logic and operators simple and pleasant to read
- Use TypeScript types/interfaces for all components, functions, and methods
- Use Next.js API routes for building APIs

### Directory Structure
Follow the next.js app directory 

### Environment Rules
- If you update environment variables, update the `.env.example` file
- All environment variables should go in `.env.local` for local development
- Do not expose sensitive environment variables
- Use `NEXT_PUBLIC_` prefix for client-side environment variables
- Use `APP_` prefix for server-side environment variables
</instruction>
